0class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3Eson%20of%20Zerahiah%2C%20son%20of%20Uzzi%2C%20son%20of%20Bukki%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_7_5%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3Eson%20of%20Abishua%2C%20son%20of%20Phinehas%2C%20son%20of%20Eleazar%2C%20son%20of%20Aaron%20the%20high%20priest.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E7%3A5%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20first%20priest.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_7_6%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20Ezra%20was%20a%20scribe%20who%20was%20well%20versed%20in%20the%20Law%20of%20Moses%2C%20which%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Israel%2C%20had%20given%20to%20the%20people%20of%20Israel.%20He%20came%20up%20to%20Jerusalem%20from%20Babylon%2C%20and%20the%20king%20gave%20him%20everything%20he%20asked%20for%2C%20because%20the%20gracious%20hand%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20his%20God%20was%20on%20him.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_7_7%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3ESome%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Israel%2C%20as%20well%20as%20some%20of%20the%20priests%2C%20Levites%2C%20singers%2C%20gatekeepers%2C%20and%20Temple%20servants%2C%20traveled%20up%20to%20Jerusalem%20with%20him%20in%20the%20seventh%20year%20of%20King%20Artaxerxes%26%23x2019%3B%20reign.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_7_8%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EEzra%20arrived%20in%20Jerusalem%20in%20August%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E7%3A8%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ein%20the%20fifth%20month.%3C%2Fem%3E%20This%20month%20in%20the%20ancient%20Hebrew%20lunar%20calendar%20occurred%20within%20the%20months%20of%20August%20and%20September%20458%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3Eb.c.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20of%20that%20year.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_7_9%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20had%20arranged%20to%20leave%20Babylon%20on%20April%26%23xA0%3B8%2C%20the%20first%20day%20of%20the%20new%20year%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E7%3A9a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Eon%20the%20first%20day%20of%20the%20first%20month%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20the%20ancient%20Hebrew%20lunar%20calendar.%20This%20day%20was%20April%26%23xA0%3B8%2C%20458%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3Eb.c.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3B%20also%20see%20note%20on%206%3A15.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20he%20arrived%20at%20Jerusalem%20on%20August%26%23xA0%3B4%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E7%3A9b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Eon%20the%20first%20day%20of%20the%20fifth%20month%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20the%20ancient%20Hebrew%20lunar%20calendar.%20This%20day%20was%20August%26%23xA0%3B4%2C%20458%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3Eb.c.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3B%20also%20see%20note%20on%206%3A15.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20for%20the%20gracious%20hand%20of%20his%20God%20was%20on%20him.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_7_10%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20was%20because%20Ezra%20had%20determined%20to%20study%20and%20obey%20the%20Law%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20to%20teach%20those%20decrees%20and%20regulations%20to%20the%20people%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_7_